                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="46142" author="tappro" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 07:00:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fix landed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="44268" author="tappro" created="Thu, 6 Sep 2012 05:43:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, I&apos;ll prepare fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="44265" author="johann" created="Thu, 6 Sep 2012 05:04:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IMHO, this bug is quite annoying and will for sure trigger user complaints.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41510" author="jlevi" created="Thu, 5 Jul 2012 15:07:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you take a look at this one?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41190" author="johann" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 07:23:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe we should put the name in the lu_device then?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41188" author="tappro" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 06:05:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d said it is not bug but design on new MDS in 2.0, there is only MDT configured from config llog and have initialized OBD device, other layers are set up by MDT and has not fully set OBD. Orion approach is different, it sets all layers from config llog. I agree that better fix for this in master would be just service name usage instead of obd_name&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41187" author="johann" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 05:25:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3160&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3160&lt;/a&gt; already stores the service name in osd_device. However, it would need a follow-up patch to fix all references to obd_name in osd.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41186" author="bzzz" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 05:19:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d say we should fix osd and do not refer obd from there, if possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
